column6: This is a study into two behaviors: exercise and smoking cessation. About each behavior we will ask sixteen questions to map how you think about the behavior. This study is a part of an international study where the goal is to compare the determinants of these behaviors over countries. For example, is it equally important for both behaviors how pleasant people find it, or what other people do? And is that the same in the Netherlands as in Finland or Croatia?
column7: This study has been set up such that all data are collected anonymously. Therefore, these can never be traced back to you. You can cease participation at any time. If you still have any questions, you can always ask these through ciberlite@a-bc.eu. Only people of 18 years and older are allowed to participate in this study. By agreeing to participate you indicate that you have read and understood this text, that you are 18 years of age or older, and do you consent to use your data, which will be collected anonymously, for scientific research.
column8: Thank you for having participated in this study!  Your contribution helps us to understand human motivation and behavior, and to what degree this is stable or different over different behaviors, countries, and cultures.  If you would like more information about this study, you can visit the Open Science Framework repository for this study at https://osf.io/mh9fs/.  You can now close your browser tab.

column49: This question is there as a trick to allow a functioning survey with an essentially empty group, so that every country can decide which extra questions to add to the ones provided by default. You can remove this question if you add other questions to the group. The relevance equation, set to '0', makes sure this question is skipped by all participants (and therefore, so is this group, unless it contains other questions that have a different relevance equation).
column50: Omdat deze studie in het Virtueel Laboratorium is opgenomen, is deelname primair educatief.  Desalniettemin is dit een serieuze wetenschappelijke studie, en daarom zijn uw anonieme data wel degelijk waardevol. Daarom worden deze anoniem verzamelde data, die dus nooit naar u te herleiden zijn, standaard openbaar gemaakt conform het Open Science beleid van de Open Universiteit, en gebruikt voor wetenschappelijk onderzoek.  Als u er bezwaar tegen heeft dat uw data in die dataset worden opgenomen, dan kunt u dat hier aangeven. In dat geval worden uw data verwijderd uit de dataset.  Als u er geen bezwaar tegen heeft kunt u gelijk op 'Volgende' klikken. [Ik geef geen toestemming voor het gebruik van mijn data, en ik wil dat mijn data worden verwijderd.]
